        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 3:31AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 330 AM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Rising Fawn to near Mentone to near Fort Payne,
and moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Naomi, Center Post, Subligna, Suttles Mill, Noble, La Fayette,
Summerville, Lyerly, Linwood, Lafayette, Menlo, Villanow, Cloudland,
Berryton, Cloudland Canyon State Park, Cooper Heights, and Trion.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
